          "architecturalNote": "PocketBase has NO native multi-tenancy. The only fully-isolated way to host N tenants is N instances → RAM grows LINEARLY (≈440,000x binocle at 100K). The alternative (one app + a manual tenant_id field in shared SQLite) keeps RAM flat-ish but funnels EVERY tenant's writes through one SQLite writer (the insert-p99 wall above, ×N load) and has no engine-level isolation (a rule bug = cross-tenant leak)."
        }
